'''Ben Tre''' (in [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]], ''Bến Tre'') is a [[Provinces of Vietnam|Province]] of [[Vietnam]]. It is one of the country's southern provinces, being situated in the [[Mekong Delta|delta]] of the [[Mekong]] River.

== Administration ==
Politically, Bến Tre is divided into seven districts:

* Ba Tri
* Bình Đại
* Châu Thành
* Chợ Lách
* Giồng Trôm
* Mỏ Cày
* Thạnh Phú

Ing tungkung lalawigan, iyapin ing [[Ben Tre|Bến Tre]], metung yang makakawaning balen.

